; palette.gtk.map — Dracula Dusk GTK-specific overrides
; Apply as a SECOND PASS after palette.map, GTK files only.
;
; Why: Dracula's GTK theme uses Pink (#ff79c6) as selected_bg_color — a design
; choice that reads as vivid accent-on-accent in this palette. This pass
; replaces the soft-pink selection with a dark-purple surface lift.
;
; Selection:
;   selected_bg_color: #454158  H:251, S:14%, L:30% — dark purple lift
;   selected_fg_color: #c8c5be  (soft-fg, already mapped by palette.map)
;
; WCAG AA compliance:
;   text on selection:  5.67:1 (soft-fg #c8c5be on #454158) ✓ text AA
;   sel-bg vs page-bg:  1.53:1 (#454158 vs #272538) ✗ UI indicator 3:1
;
; The 1.53:1 UI-indicator gap is intentional — selection is perceived via
; the text colour change (warm grey on near-black purple), not a halo boundary.
; Most professional dark themes make the same trade-off.

; Pink (already softened to #e890c3 by palette.map) -> dark purple selection
#e890c3=#454158
